40 “The bride of Christ was not nurtured
41 with my blood, with Linus’s, with Cletus’s,
42 to be used for the acquisition of gold;

46 It was not our intention that on the right hand
47 of our successors part should sit,
48 part on the other, of the Christian people;

49 nor that the keys that were granted to me
50 should become a seal on a banner
51 that would fight against the baptized;

61 But the high providence, which with Scipio
62 defended the glory of the world for Rome,
63 will come to the rescue soon, as I understand;

79 From the time that I had first looked
80 I saw myself moved throughout the entire arc
81 that the first clime makes from the middle to the end;

85 And more of the site of this flowerbed would have been revealed to me;
86 but the sun was proceeding under my feet,
87 divided into one sign and more.

88 My enamored mind, which always makes a lady
89 of my lady, burned more than ever to turn
90 my eyes toward her;

106 “The nature of the world, which quiets
107 the center and moves all the rest around it,
108 begins here as if from its goal;

115 Its motion is not distinguished by anything else,
116 but the others are measured by this one,
117 just as ten by half and by fifth;

124 The will flourishes well in men;
125 but the continual rain
126 turns the true roses into wild roses.

130 Such a one, still babbling, fasts,
131 who later devours, with loosened tongue,
132 any food in any month;

139 You, so that you may not marvel,
140 consider that on earth there is no one who governs;
141 whence the human family goes so astray.

145 that fortune, which is so awaited,
146 will turn the sterns where the prows are,
147 so that the fleet will run straight;
